<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-06-30T00:34:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-06-30T00:34:00-05:00" n="716" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d716">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/2591: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The President of the Technical Board</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Stevens</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Harbin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-06-30T14:00:00+08:26"><hi rend="italic">June 30,
                                        1922—2 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received July 1—1:27
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Technical Board resolves that by reason of absolute inefficiency of the
                            Chinese forces guarding Chinese Eastern resulting in destruction of
                            property, harassing and killing employees by bandits, <pb facs="1021" n="901" xml:id="pg_901"/> each representative shall so advise his
                            Government and ask immediate steps be taken to provide proper guard.
                            Copy Peking, Tokio.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stevens</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>